Fig. 2
). One cubito-anal Cx in all wings; Ax in FW 14 , in HW 12 (L) and 10 (R); Px in Fw 8 (L) and 9 (R), in HW 10 (L) and 9 (R); FW triangle with 4 (L) and 3 (R) Cx, HW triangle with a single Cx; FW subtriangle with 5 (L) and 6 (R) cells; FW discoidal field starting with 4 cell rows for a space of one cell length, then decreasing to 3 rows at commencement of Rspl, at hind margin increasing to 12 (LFW) and 11 (RFW) rows, 3 paranal cells in HW; FW bridge Cx 2 , HW bridge Cx 1 ; FW Pt orange, 4.62 mm long, with 3 (R) or ( 4 ) Cx immediately below, in HW 4.81 mm long with 3 Cx immediately below.
